#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:5(title)
msgid "Release 9.0alpha4"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:7(title)
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:8(para)
msgid "PostgreSQL alpha releases are snapshots of development code. They are intended to preview and test upcoming features and to provide the possibility for early feedback. They should not be used in production installations or active development projects. While the PostgreSQL code is continuously subject to a number of automated and manual tests, alpha releases might have serious bugs. Also features may be changed incompatibly or removed at any time during the development cycle."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:18(para)
msgid "The development cycle of a PostgreSQL major release alternates between periods of development and periods of integration work, called commit fests, normally one month each. Alpha releases are planned to be produced at the end of every commit fest, thus every two months. Since the first commit fest starts within a month from the beginning of development altogether, early alpha releases are not indicative of the likely feature set of the final release."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:27(para)
msgid "The release notes below highlight user visible changes and new features. There are normally numerous bug fixes and performance improvements in every new snapshot of PostgreSQL, and it would be too bulky to attempt to list them all. Note that many bug fixes are also backported to stable releases of PostgreSQL, and you should be using those if you are looking for bug-fix-only upgrades for your current installations."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:36(para)
msgid "The release notes are cumulative over all alpha releases. Items that are new in the latest alpha release are <emphasis>emphasized</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:43(title)
msgid "Migration"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:44(para)
msgid "To upgrade from any release to an alpha release or from an alpha release to any other release will most likely require a dump/restore upgrade procedure. It may happen that this is not necessary in particular cases, but that is not verified beforehand. (The server will warn you in any case when a dump/restore is necessary if you attempt to use it with an old data directory.) Note, however, that the dump/restore upgrade procedure is expected to work for alpha releases, and problems in this area should be reported."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:57(title)
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:58(para)
msgid "The primary reason we release alphas is to get users to test new features as early as possible. If you are interested in helping with organized testing, please see <ulink url=\"http://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/HowToBetaTest\">the testing information page</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:67(title)
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:69(title)
msgid "SQL Features"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:73(emphasis)
msgid "Disallow comments on columns of relation types other than tables, views, and composite types, that is, sequences and TOAST tables."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:80(emphasis)
msgid "Adjust naming of indexes and their columns. Index expression columns are now named after the FigureColname result for their expressions, rather than always being \"pg_expression_N\". Digits are appended to this name if needed to make the column name unique within the index. Default names for indexes and associated constraints now include the column names of all their columns, not only the first one as in previous practice."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:92(emphasis)
msgid "Allow the index name to be omitted in CREATE INDEX, causing the system to choose an index name the same as it would do for an unnamed index constraint. A necessary side-effect is to promote the word CONCURRENTLY to a more reserved status; it can't be a table/column/index name anymore unless quoted."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:102(emphasis)
msgid "Improve the handling of SET CONSTRAINTS commands by having them search pg_constraint before searching pg_trigger. This allows saner handling of corner cases."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:109(emphasis)
msgid "Typed table feature; this adds the CREATE TABLE name OF type command."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:115(emphasis)
msgid "Tighten integrity checks on ALTER TABLE ... RENAME COLUMN in inheritance hierarchies."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:121(emphasis)
msgid "Replace the pg_listener-based LISTEN/NOTIFY mechanism with an in-memory queue. In addition, add support for a \"payload\" string to be passed along with each notify event."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:127(emphasis)
msgid "This implementation should be significantly more efficient than the old one, and is also more compatible with Hot Standby usage. There is not yet any facility for HS standby servers to receive notifications generated on the master, although such a thing is possible in future."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:136(emphasis)
msgid "Have SELECT and CREATE TABLE AS queries return a row count. While this is invisible in psql, other interfaces, like libpq, make this value visible."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:143(emphasis)
msgid "Extend the set of frame options supported for window functions. This allows the frame to start from CURRENT ROW (in either RANGE or ROWS mode), and it also adds support for ROWS n PRECEDING and ROWS n FOLLOWING start and end points."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:151(para)
msgid "Add DO statement to support execution of procedural language code without having to create a function for it."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:157(para)
msgid "Support use of function argument names to identify which actual arguments match which function parameters. The syntax uses AS, for example funcname(value AS arg1, anothervalue AS arg2)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:165(para)
msgid "Remove previously deprecated configuration parameter add_missing_from. The system now always behaves as though add_missing_from were off."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:172(para)
msgid "Performance and behavioral improvements in UPDATE, DELETE, and SELECT FOR UPDATE/SHARE queries with joins. Fix various corner cases that could have resulted in duplicated output rows. Set-returning functions are now prohibited in the target list of SELECT FOR UPDATE/SHARE. FOR UPDATE does not propagate into a WITH query anymore."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:182(para)
msgid "Fix SELECT FOR UPDATE/SHARE in conjunction with LIMIT. Previously, it could return fewer rows than the limit specified."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:188(para)
msgid "Add a WHEN clause to CREATE TRIGGER, allowing a boolean expression to be checked to determine whether the trigger should be fired."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:192(para)
msgid "For BEFORE triggers this is mostly a matter of spec compliance; but for AFTER triggers it can provide a noticeable performance improvement, since queuing of a deferred trigger event and re-fetching of the row(s) at end of statement can be short-circuited if the trigger does not need to be fired."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:201(para)
msgid "Add exclusion constraints, which generalize the concept of uniqueness to support any indexable commutative operator, not just equality. Two rows violate the exclusion constraint if \"row1.col OP row2.col\" is TRUE for each of the columns in the constraint."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:210(para)
msgid "Support ORDER BY within aggregate function calls, at long last providing a non-kluge method for controlling the order in which values are fed to an aggregate function. At the same time eliminate the old implementation restriction that DISTINCT was only supported for single-argument aggregates."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:217(para)
msgid "Behavioral change: formerly, agg(DISTINCT x) dropped null values of x unconditionally. Now, it does so only if the aggregate's transition function is strict; otherwise nulls are treated as DISTINCT normally would, i.e., you get one copy."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:225(para)
msgid "Add SQL-compliant triggers on columns, which fire only if certain columns are named in the UPDATE's SET list."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:231(para)
msgid "Add CREATE LIKE INCLUDING COMMENTS and STORAGE, and INCLUDING ALL shortcut to allow users to make an exact copy of a table including all options and features."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:238(para)
msgid "Define a new, more extensible syntax for COPY options in order to support additional COPY options in the future."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:244(para)
msgid "Modify the definition of window-function PARTITION BY and ORDER BY clauses so that their elements are always taken as simple expressions over the query's input columns. This fixes a bug."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:252(para)
msgid "Fix bug with nested WITH RECURSIVE statements."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:257(para)
msgid "Add surrogate pair support for U&amp; string and identifier syntax."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:263(para)
msgid "Add Unicode escapes in E'...' strings."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:268(para)
msgid "DROP COLUMN and DROP CONSTRAINT now support an IF EXISTS clause so that users can avoid fatal errors when running repeatable scripts."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:274(para)
msgid "UNIQUE constraints can now be DEFERRABLE. This is primarily useful for incremental updates of numerical keys, e.g. \"ID = ID + 1\""
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:281(para)
msgid "Allow parentheses around the query expression that follows a WITH clause."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:287(para)
msgid "INFORMATION_SCHEMA, a catalog of standard views of database objects, has been updated to the SQL:2008 standard."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:293(para)
msgid "Change character_octet_length to more sensible values in INFORMATION_SCHEMA."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:299(para)
msgid "Allow * as parameter for FORCE QUOTE for COPY CSV, so that all columns will be quoted."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:307(title)
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:311(emphasis)
msgid "Support \"x IS NOT NULL\" clauses as index-scan conditions."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:317(emphasis)
msgid "When estimating the selectivity of an inequality \"column &gt; constant\" or \"column &lt; constant\", and the comparison value is in the first or last histogram bin or outside the histogram entirely, try to fetch the actual column min or max value using an index scan (if there is an index on the column). If successful, replace the lower or upper histogram bound with that value before carrying on with the estimate. This limits the estimation error caused by moving min/max values when the comparison value is close to the min or max."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:331(emphasis)
msgid "Generic implementation of red-black binary tree. For now, only GIN uses it during index creation. Using self-balanced tree greatly speeds up index creation in corner cases with preordered data."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:338(para)
msgid "Allow rewriting forms of ALTER TABLE to skip WAL logging."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:344(para)
msgid "Speed up INFORMATION_SCHEMA's privilege views."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:349(para)
msgid "Make TRUNCATE do truncate-in-place when processing a relation that was created or previously truncated in the current (sub)transaction."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:356(para)
msgid "Implement \"join removal\" for cases where the inner side of a left join is unique and is not referenced above the join. This should speed up many ORM-generated and reporting tool queries."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:363(para)
msgid "Remove the use of the flat files pg_auth and pg_database in order to improve performance. (Warning: pgbouncer and possibly other tools currently suggest referring to the pg_auth file for its user database. Such schemes will no longer work.)"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:371(para)
msgid "EXPLAIN allows output of plans in XML, JSON, or YAML format for automated processing of explain plans by analysis or visualization tools."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:377(para)
msgid "EXPLAIN now supports the use of generic options in EXPLAIN ( option value, ... ) format, which permits the creation of additional EXPLAIN options."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:384(para)
msgid "ALTER TABLE ... ALTER COLUMN ... SET STATISTICS DISTINCT allows users to manually tweak the number of distinct values estimated for a column, to fix cases where ANALYZE estimates are incorrect."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:391(para)
msgid "Make GEQO's planning deterministic by having it start from a predictable random number seed each time."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:397(para)
msgid "Rewrite GEQO's gimme_tree function so that it always finds a legal join sequence. Previously, it could have failed to produce a plan in some cases."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:404(para)
msgid "Tweak TOAST code so that columns marked with MAIN storage strategy are not forced out-of-line unless that is necessary to make the row fit on a page. Previously, they were forced out-of-line if needed to get the row down to the default target size (1/4th page)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:412(para)
msgid "Simplify the forms foo &lt;&gt; true and foo &lt;&gt; false to foo = false and foo = true during query optimization."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:418(para)
msgid "Avoid per-send() system calls to manage SIGPIPE in libpq, if the platform provides either sockopt(SO_NOSIGPIPE) or the MSG_NOSIGNAL flag to send()."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:427(title)
msgid "Administration and Monitoring"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:431(emphasis)
msgid "Add the ability to store inheritance-tree statistics in pg_statistic, and teach ANALYZE to compute such stats for tables that have subclasses."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:438(emphasis)
msgid "Revise pgstat's tracking of tuple changes to improve the reliability of decisions about when to auto-analyze. The previous code depended on n_live_tuples + n_dead_tuples - last_anl_tuples, where all three of these numbers could be bad estimates from ANALYZE itself. Even worse, in the presence of a steady flow of HOT updates and matching HOT-tuple reclamations, auto-analyze might never trigger at all, even if all three numbers are exactly right, because n_dead_tuples could hold steady."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:451(emphasis)
msgid "Support ALTER TABLESPACE name SET/RESET ( tablespace_options ), currently supporting seq_page_cost and random_page_cost as parameters."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:458(emphasis)
msgid "New faster implementation of VACUUM FULL. The old idiom of using CLUSTER instead of VACUUM FULL for speed is now obsolete."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:465(emphasis)
msgid "Add buffer access counters to pg_stat_statements."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:471(emphasis)
msgid "Add some simple support and documentation for using process-specific oom_adj settings to prevent the postmaster from being OOM-killed on Linux systems."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:478(emphasis)
msgid "Place tablespace directories in their own subdirectory so pg_migrator can upgrade clusters without renaming the tablespace directories."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:485(emphasis)
msgid "Introduce Streaming Replication."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:490(emphasis)
msgid "Add pg_table_size() and pg_indexes_size() to provide more user-friendly wrappers around the pg_relation_size() function."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:497(emphasis)
msgid "Add pg_stat_reset_shared('bgwriter') to reset the cluster-wide shared statistics of the bgwriter."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:503(emphasis)
msgid "Replace ALTER TABLE ... SET STATISTICS DISTINCT with a more general mechanism. Attributes can now have options, just as relations and tablespaces do, and the reloptions code is used to parse, validate, and store them."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:512(emphasis)
msgid "Fix longstanding gripe that we check for 0000000001.history at start of archive recovery, even when we know it is never present."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:519(emphasis)
msgid "Make standby server continuously retry restoring the next WAL segment with restore_command, if the connection to the primary server is lost. This ensures that the standby can recover automatically, if the connection is lost for a long time and standby falls behind so much that the required WAL segments have been archived and deleted in the master."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:528(emphasis)
msgid "This also makes standby_mode useful without streaming replication; the server will keep retrying restore_command every few seconds until the trigger file is found. That's the same basic functionality pg_standby offers, but without the bells and whistles."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:537(emphasis)
msgid "Add functions to reset the statistics counter for a single table/index or a single function."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:543(emphasis)
msgid "Augment EXPLAIN output with more details on Hash nodes."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:549(emphasis)
msgid "Reindexing shared system catalogs is now fully transactional and crash-safe."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:554(para)
msgid "Allow read-only connections during recovery, also known as Hot Standby. This provides a built-in master-standby replication solution."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:561(para)
msgid "Provide a parenthesized-options syntax for VACUUM, analogous to that recently adopted for EXPLAIN. This will allow additional options to be implemented in future without having to make them fully-reserved keywords. The old syntax remains available for existing options, however."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:570(para)
msgid "Add support for an application_name parameter, which is displayed in pg_stat_activity and recorded in log entries."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:576(para)
msgid "Fix longstanding problems in VACUUM caused by untimely interruptions."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:582(para)
msgid "Add YAML to list of EXPLAIN formats."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:587(para)
msgid "Add an EXPLAIN (BUFFERS) option to show buffer-usage statistics."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:592(para)
msgid "Add a hook to let loadable modules get control at ProcessUtility execution, and use it to extend contrib/pg_stat_statements to track utility commands."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:599(para)
msgid "Add a Boolean server configuration parameter \"bonjour\" to control whether a Bonjour-enabled build actually attempts to advertise itself via Bonjour."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:606(para)
msgid "When reloading postgresql.conf, log what parameters actually changed."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:612(para)
msgid "Make it possibly to specify server configuration parameters per user-database combination. Add a \\drds command to psql to display the settings."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:619(para)
msgid "Allow the collection of statistics on sequences."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:624(para)
msgid "Increase the maximum value of extra_float_digits to 3, and have pg_dump use that value when the backend is new enough to allow it, because it is possible to need 3 extra digits for float4 values (but not for float8 values)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:632(para)
msgid "Add the ability to include the SQLSTATE error code of any error messages in the PostgreSQL activity log with the new log_line_prefix placeholder %e."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:639(para)
msgid "Show the exact value being complained of in unique-constraint-violation error messages, including unique-index build failures."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:648(title)
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:652(emphasis)
msgid "Add support for RADIUS authentication."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:656(para)
msgid "When querying a table with child tables, do not check permissions on the child tables, only on the parent table. The old behavior was found to be useless and confusing in virtually all cases, and also contrary to the SQL standard."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:664(para)
msgid "Add a hook to CREATE/ALTER ROLE to allow an external module to check the strength of database passwords, and create a sample implementation of such a hook as a new contrib module \"passwordcheck\"."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:672(para)
msgid "Add large object access control."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:677(para)
