#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:991(para)
msgid "Remove PL/pgSQL's RENAME declaration, which has bizarre and mostly nonfunctional behavior, and is so little used that no one has been interested in fixing it. To ensure that possible uses are covered, remove the ALIAS declaration's arbitrary restriction that only $n identifiers can be aliased."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:1001(para)
msgid "The PL/pgSQL parser and scanner were reworked to behave much more sanely:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:1005(para)
msgid "A variable reference will only be recognized where it can validly go, ie, a place where a column value or parameter would be legal, instead of the former behavior that would replace any textual match including table names and column aliases (leading to syntax errors later on)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:1012(para)
msgid "When a name could refer either to a PL/pgSQL variable or a table column, PL/pgSQL formerly always assumed the variable was meant, sometimes resulting in surprising behavior. Now, PL/pgSQL can assume the variable is meant, or assume the table column is meant, or throw an error in ambiguous cases. For safety the default is to throw error. To configure this see <link linkend=\"plpgsql-var-subst\">the PL/pgSQL documentation</link>."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/release-alpha.xml:1021(para)
msgid "Error reporting is much nicer: it no longer shows edited versions of statements that look significantly different from what you wrote."
